<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.perfugium.com/dagger.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Looks like our summoning spell icons will be a little more specific as to what item we are summoning.<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
One other thing that caught my eye: go to test and make a new character. Each class starts out in its own &quot;creation chamber,&quot; and they are worth exploring a bit. Maybe I'm biased, but the magician chamber is one of the niftiest of the lot.<br>
<br>
The mage creation room is...The Magician's Tower.<br>
<br>
There is also an option, when you choose a character from the character select menu, to explore your class's creation chamber. When you are exploring, you can see all of your other characters standing around in the chamber as well. Clicking on one of them changes to their chamber and their perspective. However, there is no way to interact with your other characters (i.e. you won't be able to trade items over to your other toons, silly twinkers).<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
Drawbacks:<br>
<br>
There seems to be some kind of memory leak with regards to the inventory screen or the merchant screen. After a few minutes of playing, those screens started to really lag out my display. None of the other windows are causing any problems though, and the inventory works fine when I start playing.<br>
<br>
Um, no other drawbacks. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uharrije.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrije</A> at: 6/26/02 6:36:06 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimaginos9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 526<br> <font color=#333333>(6/25/02 11:42:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: OMFG</span><hr size=1> Absor they seemed to have fixed it when i logged back in. The roam feature is nice. Each class has a &quot;place&quot; they roam.<br>
